article.headline: SE Missouri 76, Cent. Methodist 63
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Jaycen Herring scored 16 points and Brandon Foust added 12 points and 11 rebounds to lead Southeast Missouri to a 76-63 win against Central Methodist on Sunday. Marcus Rhodes scored 12 points and Michael Rembert had 10 for the Redhawks, who overcame an 11-point first-half deficit. Central Methodist's Sid Stanley hit three 3-pointers in the first five minutes of the game and the Eagles built a 23-14 lead midway through the half. Southeast Missouri rallied with a 21-7 run to take a 35-31 lead into halftime. The Redhawks extended their lead to 41-33 a few minutes into the second half before Central Methodist (5-9) went on a 10-2 run to tie the game at 43-43. Southeast Missouri (9-5), whose bench outscored the Eagles' bench 36-6, scored the next six points and didn't trail again. Stanley led all scorers with 19 points. Anthony Love had 17 and Matt Sherman added 11 for the Eagles.
